cohortName: Transient cerebral ischemia referent incident cohort

logicDescription: Persons with condition occurrence of referent concept (373503) or descendants, for the first time in the person's history, with at least 365 days of prior continuous observation. Persons exit cohort at the end of the observation period.

cohortName: FDA AESI Non-hemorrhagic stroke IP events
logicDescription: All events of Non-hemorrhagic stroke (i.e. ischemic stroke) limited to events with overlapping inpatient stay with no such events in prior clean window period (365 days). No continuous observation period requirement. Persons exit the cohort on start_date + 1 day. Note: cerebral thrombosis (based on validated literature review)

logicDescription: All events of Non-hemorrhagic stroke (i.e. ischemic stroke) limited to events with overlapping inpatient stay. No continuous observation period requirement. Persons exit the cohort on start_date + 365 days. Note: cerebral thrombosis (based on validated literature review)
